               <code code="42229-5" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="SPL UNCLASSIFIED SECTION"/>
               <title>
                  <content styleCode="bold">Dose Volume Calculation</content>
               </title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Table 3 provides the required factors for the determination of activity per mL post calibration date for GLOFIL-125 sterile solution.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph> To determine the dose volume, locate the decay factor (fraction remaining) which corresponds to the day that the dose is to be administered. The following equation is then utilized to determine the dose volume:</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="underline">                        activity of desired dose                            </content>﻿   =     dose </paragraph>
                  <paragraph>decay factor x amount of activity/mL on calibration day                  volume (mL)</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>                           (information on label)                              </paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20191213"/>
            </section>
         </component>
